# Android / iOS bottom safe area on screens

Scrollable pages must not let content sit under the system navigation bar or home indicator.

## Required pattern

For `ListView`, `SingleChildScrollView`, `CustomScrollView`, and similar full-height scroll bodies inside a `Scaffold`:

```dart
import '../widgets/screen_body_padding.dart';

ListView(
  padding: screenBodyScrollPadding(context),
  children: [...],
)
```

Use `screenBodyScrollPadding(context, content: …)` when the base padding is not uniform (e.g. `EdgeInsets.fromLTRB(16, 0, 16, 24)`).

## Helpers (`mobile/lib/widgets/screen_body_padding.dart`)

| Helper | Use |
| --- | --- |
| `screenBodyScrollPadding(context)` | Standard 16 px padding + bottom inset |
| `screenBottomSafeInset(context)` | Raw `MediaQuery.viewPaddingOf(context).bottom` |
| `kScreenBodyPadding` | Default `EdgeInsets.all(16)` before inset |

## When `SafeArea` alone is enough

`Scaffold(body: SafeArea(child: …))` is fine for non-scroll fixed layouts. For scroll views, prefer **padding on the scroll view** so the last item can scroll above the nav bar — not only the initial viewport.

## Do not

- Ship a new screen with only `const EdgeInsets.all(16)` on a `ListView` body.
- Use `viewInsets.bottom` for this (keyboard inset); use `viewPadding.bottom` (system UI).
